Raw sockets provide low-level network access for custom packet capture applications.

**Raw Socket Capabilities:**
• Direct access to IP layer
• Custom packet crafting
• Protocol implementation
• Network monitoring applications
• Security tool development

**C# Raw Socket Example:**
```csharp
using System;
using System.Net;
using System.Net.Sockets;

public class RawSocketSniffer
{
    private Socket socket;

    public void StartSniffing()
    {
        socket = new Socket(AddressFamily.InterNetwork, 
                           SocketType.Raw, 
                           ProtocolType.IP);

        socket.Bind(new IPEndPoint(IPAddress.Any, 0));
        socket.SetSocketOption(SocketOptionLevel.IP, 
                              SocketOptionName.HeaderIncluded, true);

        byte[] byTrue = new byte[4] {1, 0, 0, 0};
        byte[] byOut = new byte[4] {1, 0, 0, 0};

        socket.IOControl(IOControlCode.ReceiveAll, byTrue, byOut);

        // Begin receiving packets
        BeginReceive();
    }
}
```

**Python Raw Socket Example:**
```python
import socket
import struct

def packet_sniffer():
    # Create raw socket
    s = socket.socket(socket.AF_INET, socket.SOCK_RAW, socket.IPPROTO_TCP)
    s.bind(("192.168.1.100", 0))
    s.setsockopt(socket.IPPROTO_IP, socket.IP_HDRINCL, 1)

    # Enable promiscuous mode
    s.ioctl(socket.SIO_RCVALL, socket.RCVALL_ON)

    while True:
        packet = s.recvfrom(65565)
        # Process packet data
        parse_packet(packet[0])
```

**WinPcap (Legacy):**
• Original Windows packet capture library
• Based on libpcap
• Windows 10 compatibility issues
• No longer actively maintained
• NDIS 5.x based

**Npcap (Modern Solution):**
• Successor to WinPcap
• Active development and support
• Windows 10/11 compatibility
• NDIS 6.x based
• Loopback capture support
• Raw 802.11 wireless capture
• WinPcap compatibility mode

**Npcap Installation:**
1. Download from https://npcap.com/
2. Run installer as Administrator
3. Select installation options:
   • Install Npcap in WinPcap API-compatible mode
   • Support raw 802.11 traffic
   • Support loopback traffic
4. Restart system if required

**Programming with Npcap:**
```c
#include <pcap.h>

int main()
{
    pcap_if_t *alldevs;
    pcap_if_t *d;
    char errbuf[PCAP_ERRBUF_SIZE];

    // Retrieve device list
    if (pcap_findalldevs(&alldevs, errbuf) == -1)
    {
        fprintf(stderr, "Error: %s\n", errbuf);
        return 1;
    }

    // Open device for capture
    pcap_t *handle = pcap_open_live(alldevs->name, 65536, 1, 1000, errbuf);

    if (handle == NULL)
    {
        fprintf(stderr, "Error opening device: %s\n", errbuf);
        return 1;
    }

    // Start capture
    pcap_loop(handle, 0, packet_handler, NULL);

    return 0;
}
```
